  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Slice the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>in half lengthways, keeping the green stalk<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> on</p><p>Score the<strong> aubergine flesh</strong> in a criss-cross pattern, then add the <strong>aubergine halves</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1609944942299-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1609944942299-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1609944942299-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1609944942299-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1609944942299-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the aubergine is cooking, peel and finely chop the<strong> brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1609944972830-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1609944972830-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1609944972830-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1609944972830-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1609944972830-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 700ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once softened, add the<strong> arborio rice</strong> to the pan with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the<strong> vegetable stock </strong>a ladle at a time, stirring continuously, for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
