          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the aubergine is tender, scoop the <strong>softened flesh</strong> out of the skins with a fork and discard the skins</p><p>Tip: Carefully hold the stalks (they will be hot!) to scrape the flesh out easily</p><p>Add the <strong>softened</strong> <strong>aubergine flesh</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>toasted pine nuts </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>to a <strong>food processor </strong>with the juice of 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span> <strong>lemon</strong>, a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>aubergine purée</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1609945390475-x200.jpg",
